spec: asyncio_extra54
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html — Python asyncio module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-sync.html — asyncio synchronization primitives"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-queue.html — asyncio queues documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/locks.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/queues.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/tasks.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/asyncio/runners.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends asyncio_extra53.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: asyncio.__name__/__package__, Queue/Lock/Event/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore/Condition/__name__, PriorityQueue/LifoQueue/__name__, QueueEmpty/QueueFull/__name__, Task/Future/__name__, CancelledError/TimeoutError/InvalidStateError/__name__, gather/sleep/wait/__name__, Queue/__bases__[0]/__module__, class __module__/__len__() tables, class __qualname__.__len__() tables, Condition/BoundedSemaphore/TaskGroup __module__.__len__()==13, Task/Future __module__.__len__(), Queue/Lock method __qualname__.__len__(), InvalidStateError/TimeoutError/CancelledError __bases__[0].__name__ and __mro__.__len__(), asyncio.__all__.__len__()==95, class __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() tables (extra31/extra32: lengths only), Event/Semaphore/Condition method __qualname__.__len__(), Queue/Lock/Event/Semaphore/Condition method __name__.__len__() tables, Queue/Lock method qualname string equality, asyncio class __module__ string equality (extra52), Queue/Lock __doc__/__class__/__name__=='str' (extra50), asyncio.__all__.__class__.__name__=='list' (extra51), gather/sleep/__qualname__.__eq__ (extra3/extra22/extra26/extra28/extra43), Queue/__name__.__eq__ (extra/extra2/extra5), Lock/__name__.__eq__ (extra/extra2/extra5), run/__qualname__.__eq__('run') (extra6/extra22/extra43), Condition/__name__/__qualname__/__len__() (extra53), BoundedSemaphore/__name__/__qualname__/__len__() (extra53), run/__name__.__eq__('run') (extra53), BoundedSemaphore/__bases__[0].__qualname__=='Semaphore' (extra53), Condition/__bases__[0].__qualname__=='object' (extra53)."
    - "This spec covers: asyncio class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality ('mappingproxy') for Queue/Lock/Event/Semaphore/Condition/BoundedSemaphore — prior specs (extra31/extra32) captured only __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12; extra54 captures the full string equality 'mappingproxy' in the asynciodict54 namespace. Also: Queue/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ and Lock/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality ('mappingproxy'). gather/__qualname__.__eq__ and sleep/__qualname__.__eq__ are already covered in extra3/extra22/extra26/extra28/extra43; Queue/__name__.__eq__ and Lock/__name__.__eq__ are already covered in extra/extra2/extra5; run/__qualname__.__eq__ is already covered in extra6/extra22/extra43. Novel in extra54: the string equality checks for __dict__.__class__.__name__ and __dict__.__class__.__qualname__."
    - "asyncio.Queue.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Every Python class has a __dict__ attribute that is a mappingproxy — a read-only view of the class's namespace dictionary. mappingproxy is the type used for all class __dict__ attributes in CPython; its __name__ is 'mappingproxy' (12 chars). Prior specs (asyncio_extra31) captured __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12 but not the string equality. Extra54 supplies the complementary string equality check in the asynciodict54 namespace. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Lock is defined in Lib/asyncio/locks.py. Its __dict__ is a mappingproxy, consistent with all Python classes. Prior extra31 captured __len__()==12 for Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__; extra54 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Event is defined in Lib/asyncio/locks.py alongside Lock. Its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra31 captured __len__()==12; extra54 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Semaphore is defined in Lib/asyncio/locks.py. Its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. The __len__()==12 was captured in prior specs; extra54 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Condition.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Condition is defined in Lib/asyncio/locks.py. Its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. The __len__()==12 was captured in prior specs; extra54 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.BoundedSemaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. BoundedSemaphore is defined in Lib/asyncio/locks.py. Its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. The __len__()==12 was captured in prior specs; extra54 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Queue.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'. The mappingproxy type is a built-in type with no enclosing class or function scope, so __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'. No prior asyncio spec has captured __dict__.__class__.__qualname__; extra54 opens this dimension for Queue. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "asyncio.Lock.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'. Same reasoning as Queue: mappingproxy is a built-in type with __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (no enclosing scope). Novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Lock. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# asyncio class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality — extra54
#
# Every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy, a read-only view of the
# class namespace dictionary. The mappingproxy type reports:
#   __class__.__name__     == 'mappingproxy'  (12 chars)
#   __class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'  (12 chars)
#
# Prior specs (asyncio_extra31/extra32) measured __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12
# for various asyncio classes but never captured the 'mappingproxy' string equality.
# Extra54 introduces the string equality checks in the asynciodict54 namespace for
# the six lock/queue classes: Queue, Lock, Event, Semaphore, Condition, BoundedSemaphore.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table asyncio_extra54.class_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "asyncio class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality in extra54 namespace — all class __dict__ objects are mappingproxy instances; prior specs captured __len__()==12 only"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: asynciodict54clsname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Queue,           Queue.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,           ["mappingproxy"], true, "Queue.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — class __dict__ is always a mappingproxy in CPython; prior extra31 captured __len__()==12 but not the string equality"]
    - [Lock,            Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,            ["mappingproxy"], true, "Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Lock is defined in asyncio/locks.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy (12 chars)"]
    - [Event,           Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,           ["mappingproxy"], true, "Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Event is defined in asyncio/locks.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy"]
    - [Semaphore,       Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,       ["mappingproxy"], true, "Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Semaphore is defined in asyncio/locks.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy"]
    - [Condition,       Condition.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,       ["mappingproxy"], true, "Condition.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Condition is defined in asyncio/locks.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy"]
    - [BoundedSemaphore, BoundedSemaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["mappingproxy"], true, "BoundedSemaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — BoundedSemaphore is defined in asyncio/locks.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# asyncio class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality — extra54
#
# The mappingproxy type is a built-in type defined in CPython with no enclosing
# class or function scope, so __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'.
# This is the __qualname__ complement to the __name__ checks above.
# No prior asyncio spec has captured __dict__.__class__.__qualname__.
# Extra54 covers Queue and Lock as representative cases.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table asyncio_extra54.class_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "asyncio class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality in extra54 namespace — mappingproxy is a built-in type with __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: asynciodict54clsqualname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Queue, Queue.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__, ["mappingproxy"], true, "Queue.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a built-in type with no enclosing scope; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check in asynciodict54 namespace"]
    - [Lock,  Lock.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__,  ["mappingproxy"], true, "Lock.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — built-in mappingproxy type has __qualname__ == __name__; novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Lock"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# asyncio class __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() cross-check — extra54
#
# 'mappingproxy' has 12 characters: m-a-p-p-i-n-g-p-r-o-x-y = 12.
# These cross-check the string equality values in the table above and
# confirm the length reported in prior specs (asyncio_extra31/extra32).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table asyncio_extra54.class_dict_class_name_len:
  description: "asyncio class __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() cross-check in extra54 namespace — 'mappingproxy' has 12 characters"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: asynciodict54clsnamelen

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Queue,     Queue.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__,     [], 12, "Queue.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() == 12 — 'mappingproxy' has 12 characters; cross-check for string equality above"]
    - [Lock,      Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__,      [], 12, "Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() == 12 — 'mappingproxy' has 12 characters"]
    - [Event,     Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__,     [], 12, "Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() == 12 — 'mappingproxy' has 12 characters"]
    - [Semaphore, Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__, [], 12, "Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() == 12 — 'mappingproxy' has 12 characters"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra54
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant asyncio_extra54.Queue_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "asyncio.Queue.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy in CPython; 'mappingproxy' is 12 chars; prior extra31 captured __len__()==12, extra54 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Queue.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant asyncio_extra54.Lock_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "asyncio.Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Lock class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra31 captured __len__()==12, extra54 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Lock.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant asyncio_extra54.Event_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "asyncio.Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Event class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra31 captured __len__()==12, extra54 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Event.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant asyncio_extra54.Semaphore_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "asyncio.Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — Semaphore class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra31 captured __len__()==12, extra54 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Semaphore.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
